atalogservice-2\",\n      \"reason\": \"Error ratio spike with client_error_ratio p99 reaching 13.44% during fault period\",\n      \"evidence\": \"client_error_ratio p99 change ratio: 2.0 (13.44% during fault)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"checkoutservice-2\",\n      \"reason\": \"Error ratio anomaly with client_error_ratio p99 at 4.21% during fault\",\n      \"evidence\": \"client_error_ratio p99 change ratio: 2.0 (4.21% during fault)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"aiops-k8s-05\",\n      \"reason\": \"Node CPU usage rate increased from 14.1% to 20.81% (38.44% increase)\",\n      \"evidence\": \"node_cpu_usage_rate median change ratio: 0.3844 (14.1% → 20.81%)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"adservice pods (all instances)\",\n      \"reason\": \"Consistent high pod_cpu_usage across all adservice pods (adservice-0, adservice-1, adservice-2) with usage at 0.6\",\n      \"evidence\": \"pod_cpu_usage: all instances showing 0.6 usage during fault period\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"tidb-tikv\",\n      \"reason\": \"IO utilization anomaly detected with p99 change ratio of 0.5862\",\n      \"evidence\": \"io_util p99 change ratio: 0.5862\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Key Findings:**\n1. **AdService is the most affected service** with severe response time degradation across all instances\n2. **Multiple services experienced error spikes** (productcatalogservice, checkoutservice, adservice)\n3. **Node-level resource pressure** on aiops-k8s-05 with increased CPU usage\n4. **Database IO anomalies** in TiDB-TiKV component\n5. **Consistent high CPU usage** across all adservice pods\n\nThe adservice appears to be the primary bottleneck, but further investigation is needed to determine if this is the root cause or a symptom of underlying infrastructure issues."}
